{"_id":"7fDaLDbMlbwufzZX","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"JgpLZkPryhl1EFab":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_vrpy2p1y0ua","path":"Pathfinder RPG - Occult Adventures Reference Library#/CF_SEP/Occult Adventures#/CF_SEP/TABLE OF CONTENTS","color":"#000000","name":"Table Of Contents","children":["nAikdwXoyWw0qYgA"],"folderPath":["temp_ejnndwopt2j"]}},"content":""}
{"name":"Conversion Notes","permission":{"default":0,"JgpLZkPryhl1EFab":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_me5w9yt8xt","path":"Pathfinder RPG - Occult Adventures Reference Library#/CF_SEP/Occult Adventures#/CF_SEP/APPENDIX","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<text type=\"formattedtext\"></text><text type=\"formattedtext\"><p>This product was converted from a printed book and PDF into a usable reference manual within Fantasy Grounds. In some cases, the text might refer to Chapter or page numbers or even print locations and copyright. These have been left in their original format and are presented exactly as they appear in the PDF.</p><p>Image are provided where appropriate and can be double-clicked so that you can zoom in and share the images with your players. The entire module can also be marked as sharable with your players while they are connected to your game.</p><p>Thanks to Paizo and the staff working on the Pathfinder Roleplaying Game for allowing us to create and share this content with our fans. I hope you enjoy it.</p><p>Wayne \"Shadowcat\" Arsenault</p><p>GM</p></text>\n            ","_id":"7mDbpLvFXI6c0TGf"}
{"_id":"8WeQTrrjpd09BryM","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"JgpLZkPryhl1EFab":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_n9ze4lixs3","path":"Pathfinder RPG - Occult Adventures Reference Library#/CF_SEP/Occult Adventures#/CF_SEP/BACKMATTER","color":"#000000","name":"Backmatter","children":["cYzizBLuHCVvj6wG","aaPbRwfErC2TfO7S","cISrx8GPPMo23oOl","bA699gG2Cjc87vRi"],"folderPath":["temp_ejnndwopt2j"]}},"content":""}
{"name":"Occult Rules","permission":{"default":0,"JgpLZkPryhl1EFab":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_5ifacq93nyc","path":"Pathfinder RPG - Occult Adventures Reference Library#/CF_SEP/Occult Adventures#/CF_SEP/CHAPTER 5: OCCULT RULES","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<text type=\"formattedtext\"></text><text type=\"formattedtext\"><p>One of the most fundamental elements of an occult game is the idea that those versed in the supernatural can use strange, hidden powers that are inaccessible to others. This chapter contains a variety of occult powers and abilities for characters to use in your game.</p><h1>OCCULT SKILL UNLOCKS</h1><p>Characters with psychic magic or the Psychic Sensitivity feat can unlock unusual uses of skills in which they're trained. With new uses ranging from the ability to read psychic impressions from an object using Appraise to the power to dowse for water and more using Survival, skills will never seem mundane again.</p><h1>AURAS</h1><p>This section expands auras to include not just magic and alignment auras but also health and emotion auras. A master aura reader can tell what conditions afflict a creature, as well as the state of that creature's emotions.</p><h1>CHAKRAS</h1><p>Ki users with psychic abilities can use kundalini serpent-f ire energy to unlock their chakras for strange and powerful effects, starting with the humble root chakra and moving up to the mighty crown chakra.</p><h1>PSYCHIC DUELS</h1><p>Practitioners of the occult can pit their minds against each other in a terrifying psychic duel. Such psychic combatants enter a mindscape where they can create whatever they can imagine to form attacks, defenses, and even manifested allies called thought-form creatures.</p><h1>POSSESSION</h1><p>This section explains rules for possession magic, both new and old, including corner cases like what happens when you try to possess someone who's already possessed.</p><h1>OCCULT RITUALS</h1><p>Occult rituals are rare and powerful rites that anyone who knows the right secrets can perform. Rituals are long and difficult to perform, and they always come at a price.</p></text>\n            <text type=\"formattedtext\"><link type=\"windowreference\" class=\"referencemanualpage\" recordname=\"reference.refmanualdata.refpage_chapter5occultrules\">^Occult Rules</text>\n            <text2 type=\"formattedtext\"><link type=\"windowreference\" class=\"referencemanualpage\" recordname=\"reference.refmanualdata.refpage_chapter6runninganoccultgame\">Running an Occult Game</text2>\n            <text type=\"formattedtext\"></text>\n            ","_id":"8r33GCK7PpWhf7UY"}
